Parsing Skills
The Lightcast dataset stores skills as JSON arrays within string columns (e.g., SKILLS_NAME, SPECIALIZED_SKILLS_NAME, SOFTWARE_SKILLS_NAME). Each posting can list multiple skills, so we parse these JSON arrays into Python lists for analysis. This approach is consistent with how Radovilsky et al. (2018) extracted and categorized skill keywords from job posting text.

def parse_json(val):
    if pd.isna(val): return []
    try:
        p = json.loads(val)
        return p if isinstance(p, list) else []
    except: return []

for col in ['SKILLS_NAME','SPECIALIZED_SKILLS_NAME','SOFTWARE_SKILLS_NAME']:
    df_filtered[col+'_list'] = df_filtered[col].apply(parse_json)
